HEADWORD: Goblet
<hw>Gob"let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>gobelet</ets>, LL. <ets>gobeletus</ets>, <ets>gobellus</ets>; cf.
L. <ets>cupa</ets> tub, cask. See <er>Cupel</er>.]</ety> <def>A kind of
cup or drinking vessel having a foot or standard, but without a
handle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We love not loaded boards and <qex>goblets</qex> crowned.</q>
<rj><qau>Denham.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Goblin</ent>⟦br⟧
